{
  "texts": [
    "Education is another promising target domain, where student-code-guided test generation has demonstrated effectiveness [81].",
    "Further empirical studies also confirm that in educational scenarios, AI can generate test cases with more comprehensive coverage than those manually written by teachers, effectively reducing the burden on instructors and improving the quality of automatic grading [7,37,172].",
    "This requires a concerted community effort to build more diverse, multi-lingual, and multi-domain open-source benchmarks to support comprehensive generalization research and promote the adoption of LLM-based testing in broader software engineering practices.",
    "RQ3 Key InsightParadigm shift from standalone generators to autonomous agents: Current challenges indicate that treating LLMs merely as a \"one-off code generator\" has reached a ceiling.",
    "Future breakthroughs lie in reshaping them into an autonomous testing agent."
  ]
}